records.addlTxt:
Defendant Riza I Mahmoud in court with attorney John Scott Schiro.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  Possess no weapons;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Court will allow probation to be terminated after 6 months if all conditions are met.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
